<ol data-start="217" data-end="2213">
<li data-start="217" data-end="509">
<p data-start="220" data-end="247"><strong data-start="220" data-end="245">Multi-exam Structure:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="251" data-end="509">
<li data-start="251" data-end="297">
<p data-start="253" data-end="297">4 FAs (Formative Assessments, each 50 marks)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="301" data-end="376">
<p data-start="303" data-end="376">2 SAs (Summative Assessments, each 100 marks: 20 slip tests + 80 written)</p>
</li>
<li data-start="380" data-end="509">
<p data-start="382" data-end="509">11 Subjects (Telugu, Hindi, English 1, English 2, Math 1, Math 2, Physical Science, Chemistry, Biology, Social, Spoken English)</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="511" data-end="627">
<p data-start="514" data-end="533"><strong data-start="514" data-end="533">Grading System:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="537" data-end="627">
<li data-start="537" data-end="627">
<p data-start="539" data-end="627">A+ (100–95), A (94–85), B+ (84–75), B (74–65), C+ (64–55), C (54–45), D (44–40), F (&lt;40)</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="629" data-end="790">
<p data-start="632" data-end="648"><strong data-start="632" data-end="648">Marks Entry:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="652" data-end="790">
<li data-start="652" data-end="718">
<p data-start="654" data-end="718">Teachers can enter only their own subject’s marks for each exam.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="722" data-end="790">
<p data-start="724" data-end="790">Each subject: marks split into slip tests, activity, written exam.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="792" data-end="1323">
<p data-start="795" data-end="815"><strong data-start="795" data-end="815">Layout &amp; Design:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="819" data-end="1323">
<li data-start="819" data-end="944">
<p data-start="821" data-end="944">Header includes logo, school name, “IIT &amp; NEET FOUNDATION,” exam name, student name, father’s name, class/section, roll no.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="948" data-end="1014">
<p data-start="950" data-end="1014">Report card with all subjects, component-wise marks, and grades.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1018" data-end="1123">
<p data-start="1020" data-end="1123">Attractive UI: blue header (#0f3d6b), bordered class buttons, clean white backgrounds, thin separators.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1127" data-end="1184">
<p data-start="1129" data-end="1184">SA2/final report is in color; others are black &amp; white.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1188" data-end="1234">
<p data-start="1190" data-end="1234">Barcode/QR code for student ID on marksheet.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1238" data-end="1323">
<p data-start="1240" data-end="1323">Digital signatures for teachers; director’s signature for SA2 with "Promoted" seal.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="1325" data-end="1823">
<p data-start="1328" data-end="1346"><strong data-start="1328" data-end="1346">User Workflow:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1350" data-end="1823">
<li data-start="1350" data-end="1431">
<p data-start="1352" data-end="1431">Index page: select class (Nursery to 10th), settings button for exams/subjects.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1435" data-end="1522">
<p data-start="1437" data-end="1522">Section creation under each class, then add students (name, father’s name, roll no.).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1526" data-end="1573">
<p data-start="1528" data-end="1573">Long-press on section/student to edit/delete.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1577" data-end="1633">
<p data-start="1579" data-end="1633">Click student to view exams, then exam to enter marks.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1637" data-end="1743">
<p data-start="1639" data-end="1743">Three-dot menu: generate marksheet PDF, Excel, hall tickets PDF (with timetable), and performance graph.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1747" data-end="1823">
<p data-start="1749" data-end="1823">Ranks shown in class, and individual marksheets/hall tickets downloadable.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="1825" data-end="1903">
<p data-start="1828" data-end="1850"><strong data-start="1828" data-end="1850">Performance Graph:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1854" data-end="1903">
<li data-start="1854" data-end="1903">
<p data-start="1856" data-end="1903">Bar diagram (per exam): subjects vs percentage.</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="1905" data-end="1988">
<p data-start="1908" data-end="1934"><strong data-start="1908" data-end="1934">Cumulative Record PDF:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="1938" data-end="1988">
<li data-start="1938" data-end="1988">
<p data-start="1940" data-end="1988">In AP Govt. format (cumulative academic record).</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="1990" data-end="2075">
<p data-start="1993" data-end="2018"><strong data-start="1993" data-end="2018">Multi-teacher System:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="2022" data-end="2075">
<li data-start="2022" data-end="2075">
<p data-start="2024" data-end="2075">Multiple teacher logins planned (future expansion).</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li data-start="2077" data-end="2213">
<p data-start="2080" data-end="2090"><strong data-start="2080" data-end="2090">Other:</strong></p>
<ul data-start="2094" data-end="2213">
<li data-start="2094" data-end="2150">
<p data-start="2096" data-end="2150">Attractive/child-friendly designs for younger classes.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2154" data-end="2213">
<p data-start="2156" data-end="2213">Visual feedback for undo/redo actions (where applicable).</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
